   {:e #blake3 "6a5bc05c4564ea3c35cc6a5b5a020ab6687ce6185b0071831e997ac392356b04" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: 317 ready tasks is unmanageable. R(t) ranking helps but volume obscures signal. Tasks accumulate from observe-crystallize-task and auto-task generation but are rarely pruned. APPROACH: (1) Add braid task archive command. Tasks older than N sessions (default 10) without any status change are moved to :task.status/archived. (2) Archived status is a new keyword value, not a deletion (C1 compliant). (3) braid task ready excludes archived tasks. braid task search includes them (with --archived flag). (4) braid task restore <id> moves archived tasks back to open. (5) braid task archive --dry-run shows what would be archived without acting. (6) The session count is determined by counting :harvest/session entities since the task's last :task/status change. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After archival, braid task ready shows <= 50 tasks. (B) Archived tasks findable via braid task search --archived. (C) braid task restore brings tasks back. (D) --dry-run shows preview. (E) No datoms deleted (C1). DEPENDS-ON: nothing. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/task.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/task.rs" :op :assert}
